            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Hmm, `f_inputlist()` doesn't use `get_user_input()` like the rest of the input functions do.  It directly calls `prompt_for_number()`, which sets `state = CMDLINE;` directly and then waits for user input.\r\n\r\n`get_user_input()` on the other hand ends up calling `state_enter()` by way of `getcmdline()`, so it processes pending timers.",
